component_text: technologies made our lives more complicated
new technologies are always great
it takes time for people to adapt them
we are informed with devices that are produced with new features nearly every day
many people often get lost
I use new Iphone which I personally think is great
even though I used it for couple months, I still do not know how to use all the features proficiently
I tried to go through all the instructions but, soon, I gave up
I found out that it is time-consuming and there are too many things to learn
technology destroys the language
people used computers or cellphones to chat with others
they created their own language to communicate
people try to type as fast as they are talking
they use a lot of abbreviations and broken language
This has gotten worse with twitter, myspace, and facebook
What are even worse, young people who are still in the early ages are exposed to them and impeded by the newly developed inventions
my younger brother does not know how to spell the words correctly and he talks to his friends with terms that I have never heard of
I have tried to correct him for couple times but he just thinks that I am too conservative
technologies allowed us to have a convenient life
it has made our lives more chaotic according to the reasons mentioned above
